HEADWORD: Tyro
<hw>Ty"ro</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Tyros</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>tiro</ets> a
newlylevied soldier, a beginner.]</ety> <def>A beginner in learning; one
who is in the rudiments of any branch of study; a person imperfectly
acquainted with a subject; a novice.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>tiro</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The management of <qex>tyros</qex> of eighteen⟦br⟧
Is difficult.</q> <rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

